{
    "text": "Good links slipping away",
    "created": "Sun, 25 Sep 2022 01:36:46 GMT",
    "type": "outline",
    "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/24/013646.html?title=goodLinksSlippingAway",
    "subs": [
        {
            "text": "Sorry to see old links not working when the linking sentence promises something very interesting. It went this way: \"Bloggers, by reading and writing freely, find and know themselves in '<a href=\"https://willwilkinson.wordpress.com/meditation/2014/01/23/old-school-blogging/\">a web of obligation and social expectation</a>.'\" The source article I was linking to there, written by Will Wilkerson, may still be out there somewhere, but who knows. Still, the idea that writing on the web can become a transformative personal and social practice appeals to me, even in the age of Bannon, etc. The hints and impulses are there, if we can only give the reading and writing practices reach and staying power, and make them more social, less isolated inside the individual's private life.",
            "created": "Sun, 25 Sep 2022 01:36:47 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/24/013646.html?title=goodLinksSlippingAway#a013647"
        }
    ]
}
